we can use existing tools to create a prototype of Comshell;

; sudo pacman -S xorg-server xorg-xinit xf86-video-{intel,nouveau,amdgpu} compton i3-wm i3status
; sudo pacman -S emacs qutebrowser mpv

; nano ~/.bash_profile
  startx
; nano ~/.xinitrc
  exec i3
; mkdir -p ~/.config/i3
; cp prototype/i3.config ~/.config/i3/config
; mkdir -p ~/.config/i3status
; cp prototype/i3status.config ~/.config/i3status/config

; mkdir ~/.emacs.d
; cp prototype/*.el ~/.emacs.d/
ELisp is terrible as a programming language,
  but it's pretty good as a command_line interface (ie as a shell, like Bash);

; mkdir -p ~/.config/gtk-3.0
; nano ~/.config/gtk-3.0/gtk.css
  scrollbar {
    min-width: 2px;
    min-height: 2px;
    background: repeating-linear-gradient(#777777, #777777 8px, #ffffff 8px, #ffffff 10px);
  }
  scrollbar slider {
    min-width: 2px;
    min-height: 2px;
    border: 0px;
    border-radius: 0px;
    background-color: #ffffff;
  }
